<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1965-03-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1965-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="301" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                        <head>301. Memorandum Prepared for the 303 Committee<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d301fn1">Source: Department of State, <gloss target="#t_INRIL1">INR/IL</gloss> Historical Files, 5412 Special
                                Group/303 Committee Records, January–June, 1965. Secret; Eyes Only.
                                Circulated to 303 Committee principals at the March 30 meeting,
                                according to an April 2 memorandum from
                                    <persName>Williams</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_VJH1">Vaughn</persName>. (Ibid.)</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1965-03-22">March 22, 1965</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <list type="subject">
                            <head>SUBJECT</head>
                            <item>Status of Termination of Manuel <persName corresp="#p_AM1">Artime</persName>ʼs Autonomous Paramilitary Group</item>
                        </list>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>In accordance with the decision of the Committee on 4 March
                                    1965,<note n="2" xml:id="d301fn2">See <ref target="#d298">Document 298</ref>.</note>
                                <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> has begun phasing-out support to
                                    <persName corresp="#p_AM1">Artime</persName>.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>
                                <p>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_AM1">Artime</persName> has agreed to
                                    cooperate in the disbanding of his paramilitary group. [<hi rend="italic">5 lines of source text not
                                    declassified</hi>]</p>
                                <p>[<hi rend="italic">6 paragraphs (1½ pages of double-spaced source
                                        text) not declassified</hi>]</p>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>